              <DefinitionShort>pertaining to being relatively heavy</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>heavy</Gloss>
                <Gloss>burdensome</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>Although the meaning of βαρύς in {S:04002300400008} is literal, the entire expression is figurative, and so it may be necessary in some languages to say ‘they fix up heavy loads, so to speak, and tie them on people’s backs.’</Comments>
